      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Driver Accountability and Accident Prevention (DAAP) Act of 2015</b></p> <p>This bill increases civil and criminal penalties for violations of:</p> <ul> <li>commercial motor vehicle safety regulations (except those for minimum financial responsibility for transporting passengers or property); and</li> <li>requirements for motor carrier employee qualifications and maximum hours of service, and safety and equipment standards.</li> </ul> <p>The Department of Transportation shall disqualify for one year, for a first violation, or for life, for second and multiple violations, anyone who has operated a commercial motor vehicle the individual knew, or reasonably should have known, had a defect that resulted in a fatality.</p>]]></text>
